---
import SiteShell from "../components/SiteShell.astro";
import "../styles/site.css";
---

<SiteShell
  title="Data Deletion"
  description="How to request deletion of Postmerce data, connected social accounts, OAuth tokens, media and publishing metadata."
  eyebrow="Account control"
>
  <section class="legal-prose">
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 3, 2026</p>

    <h2>How to request deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Send an email to <a href="mailto:privacy@postmerce.pl">privacy@postmerce.pl</a>
      from the email address associated with your Postmerce access. Use the subject
      line:
    </p>

    <pre><code>Postmerce data deletion request</code></pre>

    <h2>What to include</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Your name or organization name.</li>
      <li>The email address used for Postmerce access.</li>
      <li>The social platform accounts you want removed, if the request is platform-specific.</li>
      <li>Whether you want connected account data only or all stored media and publishing metadata removed.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we delete</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your request, we delete OAuth tokens, connected account records,
      uploaded media, thumbnails, captions, schedules, publishing jobs and stored
      publishing results.
    </p>

    <h2>What may remain</h2>
    <p>
      We may retain minimal operational records if required for security, abuse
      prevention, troubleshooting or legal obligations. We do not retain OAuth tokens
      after a deletion request is completed.
    </p>

    <h2>Platform-side deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Removing data from Postmerce does not remove content already published to
      third-party platforms. You can delete published content directly in the relevant
      platform account, such as YouTube Studio, Meta Business Suite, TikTok or LinkedIn.
    </p>

    <h2>Timeline</h2>
    <p>
      We aim to process deletion requests within 30 days. If we need more information
      to verify the request, we will reply to the email address used for the request.
    </p>
  </section>
</SiteShell>
